      "content": "That's a fair point, the edge case handling is definitely a priority. \n\nThe concern from the CTO is that if these weights are too \"bespoke,\" we might actually be better off just letting the Gemini cluster learn from the raw transaction data from scratch rather than trying to port over potentially outdated logic. They're worried that keeping your specific heuristics might actually hold back the new system's performance.\n\nGiven that, do you think there's any risk to the ledger's stability if we skip the weight transfer and just go with a fresh deployment on the new cluster? Or is there a reason we absolutely shouldn't just wipe the current instance and start fresh with Gemini?",
